1.1 Visualisation Applications of Simulations
A crucial step in the simulation process is visualisation, which converts complicated numerical outputs into understandable graphical representations that help in decision-making (Rossetti, 2015). Without efficient visualisation, non-technical stakeholders would not be able to access the data produced by simulation models, which would limit the value of simulation as a tool for decision support. Because graphical representations make errors easier to spot, visualisation helps with both model validation and resulting communication (Fishman, 2001).



Visualisation serves Yellowstone Inc. in a number of important ways including allowing operations managers to monitor the structure of the delivery process in real time, helping with the presentation of findings to senior leadership and enabling situation comparison. It also enables our analysts to display results from various simulation runs to determine the best course of action.

